            <section xml:id="classdialogbox_1a44b14d7932ab0866ba2d3708d406bfb7">
                <title>dialogbox::dialogbox (std::string box_path, std::string font_path, sf::Vector2f position)</title> <emphasis>Constructor.</emphasis>
                
<para>This method will create a object of this class.</para>

<para><formalpara><title>Parameters: </title></formalpara>
</para>

<para>box path : std::string 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
-&gt; The path which contains the background of the dialogbox. 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
 font_path : std::string 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
-&gt; The path which contains font of the text in the dialogbox. 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
 position : sf::vector2f 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
-&gt; This is the position of the dialogbox on the screen. 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
 <formalpara><title>Example: </title></formalpara>
</para>

<para>dialogbox d(&quot;background.png&quot;, &quot;font.ttf&quot;, {200, 800}); </para>

            </section>
            <section xml:id="classdialogbox_1a722438dee05d120c77871b1ec9d26cf5">
                <title>void dialogbox::draw (sf::RenderWindow &amp;window)</title> <emphasis>Draw the dialogbox.</emphasis>
                
<para>This method draws the dialogbox on the screen.</para>

<para><formalpara><title>Parameters: </title></formalpara>
</para>

<para>window : sf::RenderWindow&amp; 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
-&gt; The window where the dialogbox is shown on. 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
</para>

<para><formalpara><title>Example: </title></formalpara>
</para>

<para>dialogbox.draw(window); </para>

            </section>
            <section xml:id="classdialogbox_1ab9d8f8b65c3a54ccaea57a941d43a176">
                <title>void dialogbox::text_input (std::string sentence, int char_size, sf::Color color)</title> <emphasis>Set text in the dialogbox.</emphasis>
                
<para>This method sets a given text in a dialogbox. 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
Also is the font size given and in what color the text should appear. 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
</para>

<para><formalpara><title>Parameters: </title></formalpara>
</para>

<para>sentence : std::string 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
-&gt; The sentence which is shown in the dialogbox.</para>

<para>char_size : int 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
-&gt; The size of the characters in the dialogbox.</para>

<para>color : sf::Color 
<literallayout>
</literallayout>
-&gt; The color of the text.</para>

<para><formalpara><title>Example: </title></formalpara>
</para>

<para>text_input(&quot;hey&quot;, 30, sf::Color::Red); </para>

            </section>
            <section xml:id="classdialogbox_1aeb83bd7a568feeb4be10a0335838ae2a">
